---

**What was fixed and why it matters:**

1. **Inline comments** (criterion 4 — syntax highlighting): `add rax, rbx  ; inline comment` now renders the comment in gray. Previously only full-line `;` comments were caught.

2. **ASM instruction set** (criterion 1 — deobfuscation): Added ~80 missing instructions — `xchg`, `neg`, `inc/dec`, `sar/rol/ror/rcl/rcr`, all `cmov*`/`set*` variants (opaque predicate indicators), `endbr64`, `bsf/bsr` (bit scanning common in crypto), SSE/AVX basics, fences. Coverage of real obfuscated code is significantly better.

3. **Copy button** (criterion 6 — export): `COPY` button in the CodePane header, flashes `COPIED` on success, with `data-testid="code-pane-copy"` for test automation.

4. **LLM transparency** (criterion 5): Amber `LLM · <model>` pill visible when pseudocode is showing, `↺ REGEN` button to force fresh generation. No ambiguity about what's extracted vs synthesized.

5. **Pseudocode prompt** (criterion 3): Changed from "beginner could understand" to expert RE analyst prompt — ctypes/construct structs, obfuscation pattern comments, accuracy-first.

6. **Basic block separators** (criterion 1 — deobfuscation): Thin horizontal rule before label lines in ASM view separates basic blocks visually. `data-block-end="true"` on terminal instructions (`ret`, `jmp`, `hlt`) for script hooks.
